The United Steelworkers of Americasaid that bankruptcy Judge Burton Liflands's refusal to act ona union lawsuit was "a gross denial of due process for 47,000retired employees of LTV Steel."    The union is seeking an injunction that would require LTVCorp &lt;QLTV> to reinstate 400 dlr monthly supplements to about7,000 retirees. The union said that the judge, at the requestof the &lt;Pension Benefit Guaranty Corp>, delayed proceedingsuntil May four. It said the case was originally to have beenheard on February 27.    The union said LTV stopped making monthly payments inFebruary after Pension went before Lifland and receivedpermission to terminate LTV pension plans covering 47,000retired hourly workers. Reuter&#3;